  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Livelihood Improvement of Farmers in Transition</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rural households</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The program increases food availability for rural communities and contributes to the overall poverty alleviation strategy of the Government of Afghanistan by fostering links between farmers and the market, thus increasing households&#x2019; incomes. The program targets rural households, strengthening community cohesion and resilience to prices shocks. Villages&#x2019; infrastructures and storage facilities are being upgraded through cash for work which injects cash into local economies while fostering communities&#x2019; production capacity. Links between farmers and markets, business, government and financial services result in increased households&#x2019; incomes. Community Working Groups  and Cooperatives are Mercy Corps&#x2019; key stakeholder in the program, together with local government authorities including the Ministry of Agriculture, Irrigation and Livestock (MAIL), Department of Women Affairs (DoWA), Local Governors Offices, Department of Refugee Repatriation (DORR) and Department of Rural Rehabilitation (RRD). Mercy Corps coordinates activities with World Food Program (WFP), which is supplying food rations in the target area and UNHCR. Activities under this action support those most affected by rising food prices and chronic food insecurity and consequently their ability to access basic food needs. The interventions create income generation and livelihood opportunities by strengthening community capacity, increasing agricultural production and improving agriculture infrastructure and storage, and linking beneficiaries to markets, business, government and financial services.</narrative>
  </description>
